The javadoc task doesn&#39;t support the nested &quot;fileset&quot; element.  At least not
the one that I have.

&gt; -----Original Message-----
&gt; From: r_waldhoff [mailto:r_waldhoff@...]
&gt; Sent: Saturday, February 16, 2002 11:06 AM
&gt; To: junit@yahoogroups.com
&gt; Subject: [junit] Re: JavaDocs
&gt; 
&gt; 
&gt; If you want to keep the test and source files in the same source tree 
&gt; (I&#39;ve used both and think I prefer it that way), then I *think* this 
&gt; will work:
&gt; 
&gt; &lt;javadoc&gt;
&gt;   &lt;fileset dir=&quot;${src}&quot;&gt;
&gt;     &lt;exclude name=&quot;**/Test*.java&quot;/&gt;
&gt;   &lt;/fileset&gt;
&gt; &lt;/javadoc&gt;
&gt; 
&gt; We&#39;ve got quite a number of sub-projects that keep test and source 
&gt; files in the same tree, but we generate the JavaDocs across multiple 
&gt; sub-projects (by copying all the javadoc-able sources to a temp 
&gt; directory and running javadoc on that), so our &lt;fileset&gt; is applied 
&gt; to a &lt;copy&gt; task, but it looks like the above should work as well..
